## Title: Ferry Service, Fort Lennox National Historic Site

### Reference Number and Amendment Number
- **Reference Number**: PW-23-01023460
- **Amendment Number**: 1

### Solicitation Number
- **Solicitation Number**: 5P300-22-0206/A

### Tender Information
- **Tender Closing Date**: 2023-03-01T14:00:00
- **Expected Contract Start Date**: None
- **Expected Contract End Date**: None
- **Tender Status**: Expiré (Expired)

### Solicited Services
- **Gsin**: V102A (Operation of Ferries)
- **Gsin (français)**: Traversiers (Ferry Services)
- **Procurement Category**: SRV
- **Notice Type**: Demandes de propositions (Request for Proposal)
- **Procurement Method**: Concurrentielle (Competitive - Open bidding)

### Contract Details
- **Contracting Entity Name**: Parcs Canada (Parks Canada)
- **Contracting Entity Address**: 30, rue Victoria, Gatineau, Québec, J8X 0B3, Canada
- **End User Entities Name**: Parcs Canada (Parks Canada)
- **End User Entities Address**: 30, rue Victoria, Gatineau, Québec, J8X 0B3, Canada
- **Contact Information**: Jaime Creaser, Jaime.Creaser@pc.gc.ca, 902-266-8592

### Mandatory Documents
The bidding process requires that the documentation is submitted within the stipulated timeframe. Mandatory documentation includes a description of the bid, in accordance with the Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement (CETA).

### Contract Period and Option to Extend
The contract duration is 3 years, with the possibility of an additional 2 one-year periods. The option to extend the contract requires Canada to notify the contractor in writing at least 30 calendar days before the contract expires.

### Security Requirement
All personnel working on the contract must undergo a security clearance, including fingerprinting for a criminal record check.

### Evaluation Criteria
The evaluation criteria for the bid will be based on the requirements outlined in the comprehensive agreement. The proposals must demonstrate a clear understanding of the services required, details of the vessel and personnel, and any experience or references related to ferry services.

### How to Submit Tender
Submissions must be made via the Government Electronic Tendering Service at www.canadabuys.canada
